      <td align="center"><img src="images/help/db02.png" style="width: 400px; height: 350px;"></td>



    </tr>



    <tr>



      <td>Appears the window for attributes selection.<br>
      <br>
A: drop-down list of the tables of the data base to which&nbsp; it has
been connected. When selecting one of them its graphical representation
will appear on the work space E.<br>
B: option that allows to see the relations established through&nbsp; a line between the tables.<br>
C: this option is useful for market basket problems&nbsp; <br>
D: option to work multiestimated tables.&nbsp; <br>
F: line that allows to make relations between attributes of two
tables.&nbsp; the result of the established relation is reflected in
query.&nbsp; <br>
G: If click becomes on one of the attributes, an icon of&nbsp;
verification appears indicating the fields used when executing query. <br>
H: space in which query is created. It is possible to edit it manually.&nbsp; <br>
I: button for query execution. <br>
J: table for execution query results.&nbsp; <br>
K: button to accept operations.&nbsp; <br>
